\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 26, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kft1665702717817.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kft1665702717817.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kft1665702717817.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kft1665702717817\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Used in a Uniface Router UST definition to indicate that this UST will only honour shared server requests.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kft1665702717817__topic_d139208e1_d139209e1_d139210e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kft1665702717817__d6650e17\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/shr</span>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kft1665702717817__section_gst_ltx_zvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d520669e58\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kft1665702717817__p_d139217e1_d139218e1_d139219e1\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/shr</span> switch for a\n        particular UST in the assignment file to specify that the Uniface Router should take the\n        lead in managing the connection between the client and the Uniface Server. This is the\n        default behavior for the Uniface Router.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kft1665702717817__p_d139220e1_d139221e1_d139222e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/shr</span> has the opposite effect of the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ex</span> switch. Use\n        the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/shr</span> switch for a particular UST in the Uniface Router’s assignment\n        file to override an exclusive connection request (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ex</span>) from the client\n        side. </p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wmj1665702544072.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/ex</a><p>Starts the UST as an exclusive Uniface Server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pjq1665702723793.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Define Uniface Server Types (USTs)</a><p>Each UST identifies a specific Uniface Server configuration. It can be defined in the assignment file of the Uniface Router, or it can be provided to the Uniface Router by a Uniface Server that has been started manually.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mdp1665702549201.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Effect of /shr and /ex Switches</a></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/adv1665702694169.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Registering Clients with the Uniface Router</a><p>For a Uniface client application to receive messages send to it via the ProcScript command postmessage by another Uniface application (client or server), it needs to be registered with the Uniface Router. You can register a client application from the command line, in the client assignment file, or in ProcScript.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrd1665702718309.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>urouter.asn</a><p>Assignment file for the Uniface Router. You can use the urouter.asn file to specify settings, paths to connectors, and Uniface Server environment definitions, such as USTs.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529192\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529192\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/shr Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 26, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Used in a Uniface Router UST definition to indicate that this UST will only honour shared server requests. /shr Description Use the /shr switch for a particular UST in the assignment file to specify that the Uniface Router should take the lead in managing the connection between the client and the Uniface Server. This is the default behavior for the Uniface Router. /shr has the opposite effect of the /ex switch. Use the /shr switch for a particular UST in the Uniface Router’s assignment file to override an exclusive connection request ( /ex ) from the client side. Related Links /ex Starts the UST as an exclusive Uniface Server. Define Uniface Server Types (USTs) Each UST identifies a specific Uniface Server configuration. It can be defined in the assignment file of the Uniface Router, or it can be provided to the Uniface Router by a Uniface Server that has been started manually. Effect of /shr and /ex Switches Registering Clients with the Uniface Router For a Uniface client application to receive messages send to it via the ProcScript command postmessage by another Uniface application (client or server), it needs to be registered with the Uniface Router. You can register a client application from the command line, in the client assignment file, or in ProcScript. urouter.asn Assignment file for the Uniface Router. You can use the urouter.asn file to specify settings, paths to connectors, and Uniface Server environment definitions, such as USTs. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}